{
  "stem": "10572.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You asked me how the hygienic condition and the food was.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it reminds me-- let me answer sarcastically.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It reminds me that one day after I came out of Buchenwald, one of my friends and neighbors saw me on the street and came to me and said to me, Fritz, you look horrible.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where were you?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I told him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said, how was the food?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I looked at him, and I said, Hans-- Hans Voges was his name-- anybody who asks this question will never know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I would give it to you in detail, you will never know what Buchenwald was all about.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We went-- at 5 o'clock in the morning, we went to the kitchen and brought in big buckets something that they called soup.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was some fish soup.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It could have been anything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was hot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had to carry it from the kitchen on the slimy, clay road.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When it was wet you couldn't hold your feet.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even just carrying those buckets, your life was in constant danger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because if you dropped the bucket, you would have been shot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That was sabotage.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So all you had to do is pray that you would get this to the barracks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And there, it was-- every one of us had around his neck in the Jew barracks, the [NON-ENGLISH], had an aluminum container, which was not washed and was dirty.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in it we poured this thing that-- whatever we called it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we got with it a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I remember that my father used to say to me, I cannot eat out of this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's too filthy.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I said to him, close your eyes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Don't look at it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But eat it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You have to keep your strength.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was our food ration.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We got a piece of bread, like a loaf of bread, in the morning.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we lived on that all day long.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you just hoped that you will ration it carefully enough, that you wouldn't run out of it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When it came to the hygienic facilities, there were none.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had dug up, near the barrack, big things that were open latrines.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ditches, big ditches, that were open latrines, with-- with trees, which you could sit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the first three days, there was a diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the most indescribable scenes, we saw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People were in pain, and there was no way of cleaning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was-- it was unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was so unbelievable that when I finally was released with a friend of mine, who, by the way, was the photographer who did this photo album, Hamlyn Fleisheke from Hildesheim-- he and I got on the train.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we smelled so horribly that we walked away from anybody, from other people, so that they were not exposed to us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Something that hits me right now, as I say, when we-- during those months in hell, I never cried.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I never had a tear.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the first time I cried was when we came to the Weimar station to get our train back home-- individually.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We were individually released.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we went to the Weimar station.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was late at night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were Jewish woman from the Jewish organization who were bringing us sandwiches and hot coffee.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] That was the first time I cried.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] You know, because we-- we were not used to humanity anymore.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And this was more than we could take.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was another unbelievable thing that is staying with me until the day I die.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The-- the [NON-ENGLISH] was the main gate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And-- and whenever you were called for something horrible or good, for your release, you were called to the main gate to [NON-ENGLISH] And it had all kinds of connotations, horror or good news.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And one day, the monotone public address system that would constantly call out names, the numbers, they called out my name.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I couldn't believe that maybe I was on the way to freedom.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And there was a small group.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I think we were maybe 25 guys standing there who were ready to be released.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And on one side of the main gate, there were cells, solitary cells, for people with famous names who were ready to be sent to-- before they were sent to the crematorium so that they could be handled individually.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And in one of the small cells, while we were standing there waiting to be released, we heard the smashing of a window and a desperate voice screaming, screaming at us and saying, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And it was a Protestant pastor, Pastor Schneider, who, in defiance to his captors, screamed at us, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the words were stilled.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And Pastor Schneider was dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
